After an <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../183/44183.xml">
ozone hole</link> moves over Springfield, <fictional_character wordnetid="109587565" confidence="0.8">
<imaginary_being wordnetid="109483738" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../300/64300.xml">
Bart</link></imaginary_being>
</fictional_character>
 and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../658/174658.xml">
Milhouse</link> are stuck inside the house. They dress up as ladies and jump on the bed, but when they do this, Bart breaks his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../351/213351.xml">
coccyx</link>. <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../279/292279.xml#xpointer(//*[./st=%22Dr.+Hibbert%22])">
Dr. Hibbert</link> informs Homer and <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<gambler wordnetid="110118844" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<democrat wordnetid="110002031" confidence="0.8">
<artist wordnetid="109812338" confidence="0.8">
<advocate wordnetid="109774783" confidence="0.8">
<creator wordnetid="109614315" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../848/29848.xml">
Marge</link></creator>
</advocate>
</artist>
</democrat>
</causal_agent>
</gambler>
</person>
</physical_entity>
 that Bart will have to use a wheelchair for the time being. When Bart goes to school the next day, the school does not have ramps for the disabled, which changes when <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<principal wordnetid="110474950" confidence="0.8">
<wrongdoer wordnetid="109633969" confidence="0.8">
<criminal wordnetid="109977660" confidence="0.8">
<gangster wordnetid="110120085" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<bad_person wordnetid="109831962" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../397/64397.xml">
Fat Tony</link></bad_person>
</causal_agent>
</gangster>
</criminal>
</wrongdoer>
</principal>
</person>
</physical_entity>
 and his construction company, "Valdazzo Brothers Olive Oil", decides to build the ramps. They build too many ramps around the school. When the time comes for Bart to use the ramps, it is revealed that his "butt-bone" has healed. <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../052/2476052.xml">
Principal Skinner</link>, however, remains confident on the future use of the ramps, which then crumble because they are made of paint, breadsticks, and shellac. Fat Tony informs Skinner that he will have to pay $200,000 for damage. In response, Principal Skinner chooses to close <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../780/64780.xml">
Springfield Elementary</link></school>
 due to lack of funds. All pleas for help (like <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../365/217365.xml">
Mr. Burns</link>) prove futile until Jim Hope, the president of a company named Kid First Industries, buys the school and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../661/24661.xml">
privatizes</link> it.</p>
<p>

At the school, an all-new staff teaches students classes about toys and marketing, which makes <fictional_character wordnetid="109587565" confidence="0.8">
<imaginary_being wordnetid="109483738" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../277/64277.xml">
Lisa</link></imaginary_being>
</fictional_character>
 suspicious when her class is asked to name a new toy that they will sell for <vacation wordnetid="115137890" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../237/6237.xml">
Christmas</link></vacation>
. Bart visits Lisa writing lines on the blackboard. When Bart leaves and turns off the classroom lights, Lisa finds light shining through the blackboard. Lisa later discovers that they are a toy company that uses children for research to make a toy, through the use of hidden cameras, tape recording and clear, two-way blackboards. She brings in her parents and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../901/64901.xml">
Chief Wiggum</link> to investigate, but they do not believe her because the room used for spying on the children was taken out and replaced. Later on, the new toy is named <automaton wordnetid="102761392" confidence="0.8">
<artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<instrumentality wordnetid="103575240" confidence="0.8">
<merchandise wordnetid="103748886" confidence="0.8">
<commodity wordnetid="103076708" confidence="0.8">
<device wordnetid="103183080" confidence="0.8">
<mechanism wordnetid="103738472" confidence="0.8">
<plaything wordnetid="103964744" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../454/207454.xml">
Funzo</link></plaything>
</mechanism>
</device>
</commodity>
</merchandise>
</instrumentality>
</artifact>
</automaton>
 (a name which Lisa ironically suggested in class) with traits that the students had suggested during a brainstorming session (including lots of firepower, which Bart suggested in similar irony). Lisa takes Bart to the KFI headquarters, sneaking past <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../230/12230.xml">
Gary Coleman</link></actor>
 (as a security guard with varying mental health). They visit Jim Hope's office and he gives them a free Funzo. Bart and Lisa like it at home (although Lisa prefers Malibu Stacy), until they discover that Funzo is programmed to destroy other toys. On Christmas Eve, with Homer's help, they steal all the Funzos in Springfield with the intention of burning them. However, Gary Coleman comes to stop them, until they get into a discussion of Christmas. Just after they agree that Christmas's <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../280/696280.xml">
commercialization</link> is a mixed blessing, a Funzo suddenly emerges from the fire and attacks them, only to be defeated by Coleman. Afterwards, they invite Gary Coleman to a Christmas dinner at the Simpson house. As for Springfield Elementary, Mr. Burns has a change of heart and decides to fund the school after all.</p>

